Synopsis: Agent Jay is sent to find Agent Kay and restore his memory after the re-appearance of a case from Kay's past.

Title: Hustle
Synopsis: Tells the story of the last months of the 20-year war in Afghanistan through the intimate relationship between American Green Berets and the Afghan officers they trained.

Title: Retrograde
Synopsis: An ex-C.I.A. operative is brought back in on a very personal mission and finds himself pitted against his former pupil in a deadly game involving high-level C.I.A. officials and the Russian President-elect.

Title: Run Hide Fight
Synopsis: Dracula, who operates a high-end resort away from the human world, goes into overprotective mode when a boy discovers the resort and falls for the count's teenaged daughter.

Title: Hotel Transylvania

Title: Kút
Synopsis: A sexually-curious teen forms an unorthodox kinship with her mentally-unstable stepbrother.

Title: Flower
Synopsis: The wild, tragic, and controversial life and career behind one of the most polarizing figures in sports culture, heavyweight champion Mike Tyson.

Title: Van Wilder: Freshman Year
Synopsis: Four college buddies embark on a road trip to retrieve an illicit tape mistakenly mailed to a female friend.

Title: Good Trouble
Synopsis: Callie and Mariana Foster move to Los Angeles and begin their lives as young adults.

Title: Kong: Skull Island
Synopsis: After the Vietnam war, a team of scientists explores an uncharted island in the Pacific, venturing into the domain of the mighty Kong, and must fight to escape a primal Eden.

Title: After.Life
Synopsis: After a car accident, a young woman caught between life and death meets a funeral director who claims to have the gift of transitioning the dead into the afterlife.

Title: The Dig

Title: Savages
Synopsis: Pot growers Ben and Chon face off against the Mexican drug cartel who kidnapped their shared girlfriend.

Title: American Vandal

In 1971, a young and disoriented British soldier is accidentally abandoned by his unit following a riot on the deadly streets of Belfast.

Title: Corner Gas
Synopsis: The life, or lack thereof, of a proprietor of a gas station, which is the only stop for miles around and a hub of action on the Prairies.

Title: Morgan
Synopsis: A corporate risk-management consultant must decide whether or not to terminate an artificially created humanoid being.

Title: Pixels

Title: Coach Carter
Synopsis: Controversy surrounds high school basketball coach Ken Carter after he benches his entire team for breaking their academic contract with him.

Title: Five Days at Memorial
Synopsis: Doctors and nurses at the intensive care unit of a New Orleans hospital struggle with treating patients during Hurricane Katrina when the facility is without power for 5 days.

Title: Regression
Synopsis: A detective and a psychoanalyst uncover evidence of a satanic cult while investigating a young woman's terrifying past.

Title: Home Team

Title: The Sleepover

Title: May
Synopsis: A socially awkward veterinary assistant with a lazy eye and obsession with perfection descends into depravity after developing a crush on a boy with perfect hands.

Title: Fired Up!
Synopsis: The two most popular guys in high school decide to ditch football camp for cheerleader camp. For the girls and for the glory.

Title: Den 12. mann
Synopsis: Holistic detective Dirk Gently investigates cases involving the supernatural.

Title: Dirk Gently's Holistic Detective Agency
Synopsis: In an alternate present-day version of Oakland, telemarketer Cassius Green discovers a magical key to professional success, propelling him into a universe of greed.

Title: Sorry to Bother You

Synopsis: Work causes a single mother to move to China with her young son; in his new home, the boy embraces kung fu, taught to him by a master.

Title: The Karate Kid
Synopsis: In turn-of-the-century Vienna, a magician uses his abilities to secure the love of a woman far above his social standing.

Title: Priest
Synopsis: A priest disobeys church law to track down the vampires who kidnapped his niece.

Title: Fatale
Synopsis: After a one-night stand, a successful married man finds himself entangled in a cunning police detective's latest investigation.

Title: Karppi
Synopsis: When Sofia Karppi discovers the body of a young woman on a construction site, she triggers a chain of events that threatens to destroy her life--again.

Title: The Gifted
Synopsis: In a world where mutated humans are treated with distrust and fear, an institute for mutants battles to achieve peaceful co-existence with humanity.

Title: Windfall
Synopsis: A man breaks into a tech billionaire's empty vacation home, but things go sideways when the arrogant mogul and his wife arrive for a last-minute getaway.

Title: Pistol
Synopsis: A prisoner becomes a lawyer and fights to overturn his life sentence for a crime he didn't commit.

Title: Mildred Pierce
Synopsis: A 17-year-old girl suffers from a condition that prevents her from being out in the sunlight.

Title: Midnight Sun
Synopsis: The affair between King Edward VIII and American divorcée Wallis Simpson, and a contemporary romance between a married woman and a Russian security guard.

Title: W.E.
Synopsis: A harmless game of Truth or Dare among friends turns deadly when someone - or something - begins to punish those who tell a lie or refuse the dare.

Title: American Housewife

Title: Silk Stalkings

Title: Along Came a Spider

Title: A Touch of Frost

Title: Not Okay

Title: Johnny Mnemonic

Title: The Last Stand
Synopsis: An awkward seventh-grader struggles to cope with inattentive parents, snobbish class-mates, a smart older brother, an attractive younger sister and her own insecurities in suburban New Jersey.

Title: The Hardy Boys

Title: He's Just Not That Into You

Title: Another Earth

Title: White Gold

Title: Deep Blue Sea

Title: Instinct

Title: J. Edgar
Synopsis: Follows different aspects of the natural world, from an expansive look into the origin of the Universe, to life on planet Earth and how its oceans function. Narrated by Morgan Freeman

Title: Our Universe
Synopsis: The story of a man who returns home on Christmas to settle his estranged mother's estate. Once there, he discovers a diary that may hold secrets to his own past and of a beautiful young woman on a mysterious journey of her own.

Title: Lovelace

Title: Summer of 84

Title: Horizon Zero Dawn

Title: Homeward Bound: The Incredible Journey

Title: Godzilla: King of the Monsters
Synopsis: In 1978, four rebellious teenagers try to scam their way into a KISS concert.

Title: Detroit Rock City

Title: Terminator 3: Rise of the Machines

Title: Eighth Grade

Title: Back to the Future Part IV: Back in Timeline

Title: Grown-ish
Synopsis: A spinoff of ABC's "Black-ish," Zoey Johnson is off to college and must live outside the nest, dealing with drugs, sex, and relationships along the way.

Title: The Firm
Synopsis: A young lawyer joins a prestigious law firm only to discover that it has a sinister dark side.

Title: The Family

Title: On the Road
Synopsis: A young Jeffrey Dahmer struggles to belong in high school.

Title: My Friend Dahmer
Synopsis: With his wife doing a book tour, a father of twelve must handle a new job and his unstable brood.

Title: The Mighty Ducks
Synopsis: A self-centered Minnesota lawyer is sentenced to community service coaching a rag tag youth hockey team.

Title: Yes Man
Synopsis: A man challenges himself to say "yes" to everything.

Title: Scrooge: A Christmas Carol
Synopsis: A supernatural, time-travelling, musical adaptation of Charles Dickens's cult Christmas story.

Title: Beyond the Lights
Synopsis: The pressures of fame have superstar singer Noni on the edge, until she meets Kaz, a young cop who works to help her find the courage to develop her own voice and break free to become the artist she was meant to be.

Title: Night at the Museum: Secret of the Tomb
Synopsis: Larry spans the globe, uniting favorite and new characters while embarking on an epic quest to save the magic before it's gone forever.

Title: A Madea Homecoming
Synopsis: Madea's back hallelujer. And she's not putting up with any nonsense as family drama erupts at her great-grandson's college graduation celebration.

Title: Out of Exile
Synopsis: After a botched armored car robbery, a recently paroled thief tries to balance his life and mend a troubled family as a determined FBI agent hunts down him and his crew.

Title: The Condemned

He is "purchased" by a wealthy television producer and taken to a desolate island where he must fight to the death against nine other condemned killers from all corners of the world, with freedom going to the sole survivor.

Title: The Old Man & the Gun

Title: Jacob's Ladder

Title: Perfect Sense

Title: By the Sea
Synopsis: A couple tries to repair their marriage while staying at a hotel in France.

Title: Bo Burnham: Inside
Synopsis: A musical comedy special shot and performed by Bo Burnham, alone, over the course of a very unusual year.

Title: Love Wedding Repeat
Synopsis: While trying to make his sister's wedding day go smoothly, Jack finds himself juggling an angry ex-girlfriend, an uninvited guest with a secret, a misplaced sleep sedative, and the girl who got away in alternate versions of the same day.

Title: The Kingdom
Synopsis: A team of U.S. government agents are sent to investigate the bombing of an American facility in the Middle East.

Title: Bad News Bears
Synopsis: A grizzled little league coach tries to turn his team of misfits into champs.

Title: Reindeer Games
Synopsis: After assuming his dead cell-mate's identity to get with the other man's girlfriend, an ex-convict finds himself a reluctant participant in a casino heist.

Title: Meet Dave

Title: Back to the Outback

Title: The Limey

Title: Don't F**k with Cats: Hunting an Internet Killer

Title: Assassins

Title: Nick and Norah's Infinite Playlist

Title: The Professor
Synopsis: A college professor lives his life with reckless abandon after being diagnosed with a terminal illness.

Title: Constantine
Synopsis: A man struggling with his faith who is haunted by the sins of his past is suddenly thrust into the role of defending humanity from the gathering forces of darkness.

Title: Killing Me Softly
Synopsis: A woman faces deadly consequences for abandoning her loving relationship with her boyfriend to pursue exciting sexual scenarios with a mysterious celebrity mountaineer.

Title: Sniper: Ultimate Kill

Title: Derailed
Synopsis: When two married business executives having an affair are blackmailed by a violent criminal, the two must turn the tables on him to save their families.

Title: Toy Soldiers
Synopsis: A group of troublemaking boys decide to take a stand when terrorists seize control of their boarding school.

Title: Bowfinger
Synopsis: When a desperate movie producer fails to get a major star for his bargain basement film, he decides to shoot the film secretly around him.

Title: Masters of the Universe: Revelation

Title: Step Up 3D
Synopsis: A tight-knit group of New York City street dancers find themselves pitted against the world's best hip hop dancers in a high-stakes showdown.

Title: No Reservations
Synopsis: The life of a top chef changes when she becomes the guardian of her young niece.

Title: Passing
Synopsis: "Passing" follows the unexpected reunion of two high school friends, whose renewed acquaintance ignites a mutual obsession that threatens both of their carefully constructed realities.

Title: Spy Kids 2: Island of Lost Dreams

Title: Leonardo

Title: Warlock: The Armageddon

Title: The Great Debaters

Title: Splitting Up Together
Synopsis: The story of a couple whose marriage is reignited by their divorce.

Title: Afternoon Delight
Synopsis: Rachel tries to spice up her marriage with a trip to a strip club. She befriends McKenna who gave her a lapdance. She moves in with Rachel's family and becomes a nanny for the son.

Title: Joe
Synopsis: An ex-con, who is the unlikeliest of role models, meets a 15-year-old boy and is faced with the choice of redemption or ruin.

Title: The Whole Truth
Synopsis: A defense attorney works to get his teenage client acquitted of murdering his wealthy father.

Title: Sirens
Synopsis: When a painting is termed blasphemous, a young minister and his wife visit the artist... and the three sexually playful models living with him.

Title: Hodejegerne
Synopsis: An accomplished headhunter risks everything to obtain a valuable painting owned by a former mercenary.

Title: An Unfinished Life

Title: Effie Gray

Title: Reign Over Me

Title: The Humans

Title: Man with a Plan
Synopsis: A dad finds out that parenting is harder than he thought after his wife goes back to work and he's left at home to take care of the kids.

Title: Kung Pow: Enter the Fist
Synopsis: A rough-around-the-edges martial arts master seeks revenge for his parents' death.

Title: The Invention of Lying
Synopsis: A comedy set in a world where no one has ever lied, until a writer seizes the opportunity for personal gain.
